<title>USA: Newport says Deuster to succeed Schmidt.</title>
<headline>Newport says Deuster to succeed Schmidt.</headline>
<dateline>IRVINE, Calif. 1997-06-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Newport Corp said Monday Robert Deuster, president and chief executive officer, has assumed the additional position of chairman.</p>
<p>As part of a planned management succession, he is succeeding Richard Schmidt, who will remain on the company's board but is retiring as chairman, the  company said.</p>
<p>Deuster, 46, joined Newport as president and chief executive officer in May 1996, having been a senior executive with Applied Power Inc.</p>
